FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://app.expan.do/api/v2

# Expando Public API (v2.100)

API documentation for app.expan.do

**Note**: The `Authorization` header has to include `Bearer` keyword.
*Example:* If your token is `5Lw1cA`, the whole `Authorization` header
will be `Bearer 5Lw1cA`.

Also note that you can consider the response successful
**only if the HTTP response status code is in `20x` range**.

# Release notes
- v2.100 - Extended `packages` field in `/fulfillment` endpoint to support Amazon marketplace with detailed tracking
- v2.99 - Changed `carrier` enum values in the `/fulfillment` endpoint. See the enum definition for all changes.
- v2.98 - Added `packages` field to `/fulfillment` endpoint, optional for Alza marketplace
- v2.97 - Added `taxRatePercentDecimal` field to `/orders` and `/orderfeed` and deprecated `taxRatePercent` field
- v2.96 - Added `buyerCustomInfo` field to `/orders` and `/orderfeed`
- v2.95 - Added `GuaranteeClaim` event type and `additionalItems` field to `/finances/orderevents`
- v2.94 - Added `parcelShop` field to `/orderfeed`
- v2.93 - Added Amazon carrier code `DHL eCommerce`
- v2.92 - Deprecated glami_cz marketplace
- v2.91 - Added kaufland_at, kaufland_pl, allegro_cz, allegro_pl, allegro_sk, limetka_cz, limetka_gr, limetka_sk, baskedo_bg, baskedo_hu, bol_nl, ebay_at, ebay_cz, ebay_fr, ebay_pl, ebay_de, ebay_us and ebay_uk marketplaces`
- v2.90 - Added `Chargeback` event type to `/finances/orderevents`
- v2.89 - Added Amazon carrier code (WEDOLOGISTICS)
- v2.88 - Added Kafuland carrier code (WEDOLOGISTICS) 
- v2.87 - Added `marketplaceOrderIds` query parameter to `/orders` endpoint
- v2.86 - Added transaction type and date to invoices on order
- v2.85 - Added CZPOSTP Post office delivery for shipping carrier code CZPOST (Parcel shop identification for Alza)
- v2.84 - Added Amazon carrier code (CTTExpress)
- v2.83 - Added Return labels (`/return-labels`, `/orders`, `/orderfeed`)
- v2.82 - Added Kaufland carrier code (SPS - Slovak Parcel Service)
- v2.81 - Added Geis to supported carriers for Kaufland
- v2.80 - Added fullNumber to Fulfillment
- v2.72 - Changed Kaufland carrier PACKETA to Packeta
- v2.71 - Added Kaufland carrier code (CZECHPOST)
- v2.70 - Added parameter (shipMethod) to `POST /fulfillment`
- v2.69 - Added Kaufland carrier code (PACKETA)
- v2.68 - Added new Alza carrier code (DPDALZABOX, DPDBOX, DPDPARCELSHOP)
- v2.67 - Deprecated real_de marketplace, add kaufland_de, kaufland_cz and kaufland_sk marketplaces

## Orders [/orders{?fromLastChanged}]

### List Orders [GET]
Returns up to 100 orders by last change date.

You can paginate naturally through orders by taking `lastChanged` attribute
of the last order on a page and making the request again with this new value in your query.

You will get an empty array once you exhaust order changes. Some pages may contain less than 100 orders, but this does not mean it is the last page.

You can also request specific orders by providing `marketplaceOrderIds` parameter in the query.
It is a comma separated list of marketplace order IDs and may contain up to 100 IDs.

Parameters `fromLastChanged` and `marketplaceOrderIds` cannot be used simultaneously.

+ Parameters
    + fromLastChanged - string - ISO date
    + marketplaceOrderIds - string - comma separated list of marketplace order IDs

+ Request

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer <token>


+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes ( array[ Order ] )

## Order Feed [/orderfeed{?access_token}{?days}]

### Get Order Feed [GET]
Returns feed which is an old version of getting orders with new parameters.

**Explanation of attributes:**

`fulfillmentChannel`:
- `Seller` - fulfilled by seller
- `MediatedCarrier` - fulfilled by a marketplace (currently used with Alza and Mall)
- `FBA` - Fulfilled by Amazon

`businessOrder` - B2B or B2C order type
`isPrime` - only for Amazon
`isComplete` - received all the information for order
`isRefunded` - is the order refunded or not
`customer` - information about the customer includes only delivery address


+ Parameters
    + access_token ( string ) - API Bearer token
    + days ( number ) - number of days to lookback


+ Response 200 (text/xml)
    + Body
