## Package Labels [/package-labels]

### Generate package labels [POST /package-labels]

Request package shipping labels for one; or multiple orders (if you're consolidating multiple orders to a single branch).

By default, a label for a *single package* will be generated. If you wish to split your order/s to multiple packages, you can provide your own `packages` parameter.

Returns 202 while the labels are being generated. Please make subsequent GET calls to a created resource to fetch the current status.

+ Request
    + Attributes (CreateLabelInput)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (PackageLabelData)

+ Response 202 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + status: Generating ( string )
        + packageLabelsId: `111-222-aaa` ( string )
        + packages ( array [FulfillmentPackage] )

+ Response 400 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + message ( enum )
            + Members
                + You can only consolidate orders belonging to the same branch.
                + `Some items(number) are not included in packages.`
                + All orders must be from same marketplace.
                + `Item with id: string doesn't exist in order.`
                + `Packages contains invalid marketplaceOrderId.`
                + `Items quantity doesn't match. Ordered: (number), Provided: (number)`
                + Please check, that every order is eligible for package-labels generation.
                + You have already requested package labels for different marketplaceOrderIds.'
+ Response 404 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + message ( enum )
            + Members
                + `Can not find resources.`
                + `Some resources were not found.`

### Get package labels [GET /package-labels/{packageLabelsId}]
Fetch package labels.

While the labels are being generated, you'll receive status `Generating` and your request should be retried after few seconds. Once the labels are generated, you'll receive status `Generated` and labels PDF will be available for download.

In case of unexpected issues with the carrier API, you might occasionally receive status `Failed` with details in `failReason` . You might retry the request with revised input.

+ Parameters
    + packageLabelsId: 111abc333 ( string )
+ Request

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Retry-After: 5

    + Attributes ( PackageLabelData )

+ Response 404 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + packageLabelsId: 11abc333 ( string )
        + message ( enum )
            + Members
                + Resource not found.
                + `Resource not found, have you requested for creation?`




### Fulfill order/s using package labels data [POST /package-labels/{packageLabelsId}/fulfill]
If you have package shipping labels generated for one or multiple orders, you can fulfill these orders directly using the data provided for shipping labels. This is a shortcut for `Update Fulfillment` action so that you don't need to provide any details
+ Parameters
    + packageLabelsId: 111abc333 ( string )
+ Request
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes ( Fulfillment )

+ Response 400 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + packages ( array[FulfillmentPackage] )
        + packageLabelsId: 123-abc-345 ( string )
        + failReason: Maximum number of required packages exceeded. Actual limit is 1. ( string )


## Fulfillment [/fulfillment]

### Update Fulfillment [POST]

We provide one generic fulfillment endpoint that supports multiple marketplaces.
However note that each platform has its own unique requirements you have
to follow for peaceful communication with the marketplace.

**Generic:**

Attributes `shipDate`, `carrierName`, `fullNumber` and `trackingNumber` are nullable.

If `shipDate` is `null`, then `shipDate` will be set to current UTC time instead.
Subsequent updates of `shipDate` will not overwrite the initial value.

Check individual marketplaces for interpretation of each status.

**For Amazon orders:**

If the `carrier` is `Other`, the `carrierName` must be set. If the `carrier`
is not `Other`, `carrierName` must be `null`.

Any updates for Amazon are currently seen as with status `Shipped` except status `Canceled` which will trigger order cancellation.

For updates with status `Canceled` only can you specify the cancel reason (`cancelReason` parameter).
If `cancelReason` is not specified, the first default value will be fetched from `cancelRequest.cancelReason` on order (only `BuyerCanceled` for now) and if there is no cancel request, then the final default value will be `NoInventory`.

> **NOTE**: `shipDate` time must be between order purchase date time and current time (UTC). Amazon will reject the fulfillment otherwise.

**For Mall orders:**

The workflow and supported statuses are as follow:
- `Registered` - seller starts processing the order
- `Shipped` - seller gives shipment to carrier
  - extra `trackingNumber` and `trackingUrl` fields need to be send in request.
- `Delivered` - seller receives confirmation from carrier about the shipment delivery (`deliveryDate` attribute is filled automatically, with actual date when fulfillment endpoint is called with status `Delivered`)
- `Canceled`
Each status will change Mall order state accordingly except `Registered` which will change state to `Shipping`.

> **NOTE**: First letter of status string is capital

**For Alza orders:**

> **NOTE**: If your Alza Dropshipment contract allows usage of marketplace-provided package shipping labels, you must use `/package-labels/{packageLabelsId}/fulfill` endpoint.

Field `trackingNumber` is always required. Status `Shipped` also
requires additional fields (see specification). Those fields are _not_ required
in other statuses.

- The best choice is to map _order's_ `delivery.shippingCarrier` to `carrierName` and `delivery.shippingCarrierService` to `carrier`
- `carrier` is one of [Alza's delivery types](https://dropa.docs.apiary.io/#/data-structures/0/shipping-carrier-delivery-type). `carrierName` is one of [Alza's carrier codes](https://dropa.docs.apiary.io/#/data-structures/0/shipping-carrier-code)
- If the `carrier` is `Supplier`, the `carrierName` can be empty or one of [Alza's carrier codes](https://dropa.docs.apiary.io/#/data-structures/0/shipping-carrier-code)
- The `packages` field is supported for Alza orders only, allowing to specify shipment details for multiple packages within an order.

The `Registered` status has no effect. Supports all other statuses.

**For eMAG orders:**

Supports `Shipped` status. Other have no effect.

**For Cdiscount orders:**

***Order acceptation:***
Cdiscount orders must be accepted and there are two ways, how to accept Cdiscount order:
- Automatic acceptation by Cdiscount. This means all Cdiscount orders will be automatically accepted. It can be turned on/off at Cdiscount seller portal.
- Manual acceptation. This means all Cdiscount orders must be accepted by seller.

Manual Acceptation:
- All orders in the "Pending" state are not accepted and must be accepted within 48 after order creation.
- There is automatic order acceptation at EXPANDO and EXPANDO will accept each order after 47 hours after its creation.
- If you want to accept order via EXPANDO API, you have to set its fulfilment to state "Registered".
- It is also possible to manually accept order in EXPANDO APP.
- If you want to cancel an order for any reason, you can do that by setting fulfillment status to “Canceled”. Be aware that you must do it within 47 hours after the order was first received.

***Order confirmation:***
- When the order is already in status `Unshipped` you are eligible to confirm that order by setting fulfillment status to `Shipped` state. Be aware that when you are changing fulfillment status to `Shipped` you will have to include tracking details (marketplace, carrier, carrierName, trackingNumber, etc.) in your request.
- If the `carrier` is `Other`, the `carrierName` must be set. If the `carrier` is not `Other`, `carrierName` must be `null`. The workflow and supported statuses are as follow:
   - `Registered` - seller accepts the order
   - `Shipped` - seller gives shipment to carrier
- `Warning: Cdiscount orders in the "Pending" state are not payed yet. A seller should wait for the state "Unshipped" to avoid dispatching unpaid orders.`

***Shipped order confirmation example:***

    {
        "marketplaceOrderId": "1111111111A11A1",
        "marketplace": "cdiscount_fr",
        "status": "Shipped",
        "trackingNumber": "22222222222",
        "trackingUrl": "https://gls-group.eu",
        "carrier": "GLS",
        "carrierName": null,
        "shipDate": "2019-02-28T14:25:00.000Z"
    }

***Cdiscount payment fees:***
- When the order contains special Cdiscount payment fees, total order price does not match sum of order item prices.
- These special fees can be found in payment property of the order.

Order Feed (/orderfeed endpoint):
```xml
<payment>
    <cashOnDelivery>
        <servicePrice>1.23</servicePrice>
    </cashOnDelivery>
</payment>
```

Orders (/orders endpoint):
```json
{
    payment: {
        cashOnDelivery: {
            servicePrice: 1.23
        }
    }
}
```

**For Kaufland orders:**

Both `Registered` and `Shipped` statuses will confirm shipment of the order. You can optionally add shipping info.
If the `carrier` is `Other`, the `carrierName` must be set. If the `carrier` is not `Other`, `carrierName`
must be `null` and `trackingNumber` must be set.

*Note: Kaufland does not allow us to change the trackingNumber once it has been set.*

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer <token>

    + Attributes ( InputFulfillment )

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes ( Fulfillment )

## PDF Documents [/branch-barcodes-batch]

### Barcodes for Branch Delivery [POST /branch-barcodes-batch]
Generate a batch of **branch delivery barcodes** in printable PDF format.

Generated barcodes have to be printed and sticked onto the specific items that are being delivered
to a marketplace branch.

You only need to provide a list of `marketplaceOrderIds` for which you wish the barcodes
to be generated in a single PDF.

*Note that you can generate barcodes only for orders that are actually delivered to branch.*

This endpoint has a timeout of 29 seconds. If the document cannot be generated in time, you will
receive an appropriate message (see section _Response 500_ for more details).

+ Request
    + Attributes (BranchBarcodesBatchInput)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (BranchBarcodesBatch)

+ Response 400 (application/json)
    This endpoint specifically responds with `400` if some of the provided orders
    do not contain any delivery barcodes; or orders cannot be found.

    + Attributes
        + message: `No delivery barcodes found for orders with marketplaceOrderIds: 1234, 5678` ( string, required )

+ Response 500 (application/json)
    It is possible for the request to occasionally time out. You will get
    response `500` and you can safely retry your request after the number
    of seconds specified in `Retry-After` header.

    + Headers

            Retry-After: 5

    + Attributes
        + message: `Generating PDF document timed out. Please try again later.` ( string )


## Pickup Lists [/pickup-lists]

### Get Pickup Lists [GET /pickup-lists{?carrierPickupListId}{?pickupDay}{?fromLastChanged}]

Returns pickup lists sorted by `lastChanged` in descending order.

Optionally, you can supply supported attributes to receive only pickup lists you want.

If you supply multiple parameters, then only one is applied, in following order:
1. carrierPickupListId
2. pickupDay
3. fromLastChanged

+ Parameters
    + carrierPickupListId: `123456` ( number, optional ) - ID of pickup list to get.
    + pickupDay: `2020-12-30` ( string, optional ) - Which day to get pickup lists for.
    + fromLastChanged: `2020-12-30T00:00:00.000Z` ( string, optional ) - ISO Date.

+ Request
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[PickupLists])




## Pricing Report [/marketplace/{marketplace}/pricing-report{?access_token}]

+ Parameters
    + marketplace ( enum[string] )
